name: 4.Model Prediction
content:
Model Prediction :


 Prophet

  • Forecasting
  • Generates future demand forecasts while factoring in manufacturing seasonality and holiday effects.
  • Visualization
  • Produces forecast plots with confidence intervals, offering insights for production planning.
  • Strengths
  • Handles irregular demand patterns.
  • Allows adjustments for factory shutdowns or operational holidays.


SARIMAX

  • Forecasting
  • Produces forecasts for future demand, leveraging both historical sales and external variables.
  • Diagnostics
  • Evaluates residuals to refine the model, ensuring robust and stable predictions for production schedules.
  • Strengths
  • Incorporates market trends, raw material costs, or supplier delays.
  • Provides deeper insights into demand fluctuations beyond seasonality.


Use Case in Manufacturing

  • Prophet is effective for capturing recurring demand cycles (e.g., seasonal peaks in production).
  • SARIMAX is more effective when external business or supply chain factors significantly influence demand.
  • Both models support inventory management, production planning, and minimizing overproduction or stockouts.




Time Series Forecast with 95% Confidence Interval :


This line graph displays a time series forecast with a 95% confidence interval, likely for sales data, spanning from early 2014 to late 2017. The x-axis represents time, with data points appearing at the end of each month. The y-axis likely indicates forecasted sales figures, potentially in millions based on the 4,000,000 maximum value.

Three lines are plotted:

  • Forecasted Sales: This line represents the predicted sales value for each month.
  • 95% Lower Limit: This line indicates the lower bound of the 95% confidence interval, meaning there is a 95% probability that the actual sales value will fall above this line.
  • 95% Upper Limit: This line represents the upper bound of the confidence interval, suggesting a 95% probability that the actual sales value will fall below this line.

The confidence interval visually demonstrates the uncertainty associated with the forecast. A wider interval suggests greater uncertainty in the prediction, while a narrower interval indicates higher confidence. This visualization allows for a more nuanced understanding of the forecast, acknowledging the range of possible outcomes rather than relying solely on a single predicted value.
